1)Foremost installation

sudo apt-get install foremost

2)Create a new directory and add files in them (video files)


3)Foremost commands

-v
Enables verbose mode. This causes more information regarding the current state of the program to be displayed on the screen, and is highly recommended.

-i file
The file is used as the input file. If no input file is specified or the input file cannot be read then stdin is used.

-t   
specify file type.(Ex: .jpg, .mp4, .img)

4)Foremost usage

foremost -v -t all -i fire.mp4

5)Foremost result:

Files extracted:2
File size: 5Mb
Partial file:1
Full multimedia file:1
File formats of output files: .mov(partial), .mp4(full)

